<div style="text-align: left">Terrestrial <a href="../../metazoa/arthropoda/arthropoda.html"> arthropods</a> very common and diverse. Many types of <a href="../../vertebrates/tetrapoda/index.html">tetrapod</a>s. Reptiles present but small and insignificant.</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="pen2">
<big><a href="moscovian.html">The Moscovian</a></big> <br />
<div style="text-align: left">While Euramerica is covered in tropical forests, Gondwana suffers glaciation and ice ages. Life abundant and diverse. Reptiles begin to diversify, but still overshadowed by amphibians</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="pen3">
<big><a href="kasimovian.html">The Kasimovian</a></big> <br />
<div style="text-align: left">Drought decimates the great Euramerican lycopods ("scale trees"), resulting in a tree-fern dominated flora. <a href="../../vertebrates/tetrapoda/index.html"> Tetrapods</a> and terrestrial arthropods remain abundant and diverse. The arthropleurids die out before the beginning of the Gzhelian</div></td>
</tr>
